article.description: E.J. Stephens scored 18 points as Lafayette topped Holy Cross 72-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Stephens scores 18 points as Lafayette tops Holy Cross 72-62
article.linkText: Stephens scores 18 points as Lafayette tops Holy Cross 72-62
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- E.J. Stephens scored 18 points as Lafayette topped Holy Cross 72-62 on Saturday. Myles Cherry added 16 points and eight rebounds for the Leopards (16-9, 8-6 Patriot League) and Tyrone Perry had 15 points with six rebounds. Joe Pridgen had 25 points and eight rebounds for the Crusaders (3-24, 2-12 Patriot League), who have now lost seven games in a row. Matt Faw added 19 points and eight rebounds. Connor Niego had 11 points. Lafayette defeated Holy Cross 82-64 on Jan. 8. Holy Cross takes on Bucknell at home on Monday. Lafayette plays at home against Boston University on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
